content: Hello! I'm pretty new to the Rust community. A few months ago, I ran into a diagnostics papercut (actually directed there by a question on StackOverflow) and decided to fix it: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/87998. Unfortunately, it's been about six weeks and I've received no replies or review at all. Did I do something wrong?
@Robert Xiao no, reviewers just take a really long sometimes unfortunately. I'll see if I can find another reviewer who's familiar with the code.
Hopefully we'll all graduate to reviewers over time to lighten the load
